  "prompt": "What is FARC?",
  "response": "The Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia, commonly known by its Spanish acronym FARC (Fuerzas Armadas Revolucionarias de Colombia), is a Marxist-Leninist guerrilla group that was involved in the Colombian armed conflict from its formation in 1964 until its demobilization following a peace agreement in 2016. FARC was originally founded as the armed wing of the Colombian Communist Party with the aim of overthrowing the Colombian government and installing a Marxist regime. \n\nThe group financed its activities through various means, including kidnapping, extortion, and involvement in the drug trade. This led to significant internal and international controversy and condemnation. \n\nIn 2016, after decades of conflict that resulted in thousands of deaths and displacements, FARC and the Colombian government reached a historic peace agreement. The majority of FARC combatants demobilized, laid down their arms, and the group transitioned into a political party known as the Common Alternative Revolutionary Force (Fuerza Alternativa Revolucionaria del Com\u00fan), retaining the acronym FARC. However, some dissident factions chose not to comply with the peace process and continue to engage in armed activities.",
